\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 1. **Thermal Decay Layer**
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 \'a0\'a0\'a0* Models the cooling of concepts after intense cognitive activity.
\fs24 \strokec2 \

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 \'a0\'a0\'a0* Transitions from Soot \uc0\u8594  Ash over time, unless reignited.
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 2. **Residual Memory Economy**
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 \'a0\'a0\'a0* Prevents \'93hard loss\'94 of information by keeping volatile residues in circulation for a limited time.
\fs24 \strokec2 \

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 \'a0\'a0\'a0* Provides Ash as a stable base for future blooms.
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 3. **Triggerable Rekindling**
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 \'a0\'a0\'a0* Active modules (Mycelium, CARRIN, Tracer systems) can tap into Soot stores to rapidly reheat fragments.
\fs24 \strokec2 \
\

\fs29\fsmilli14667 \strokec2 ---
